getFileName

public String getFileName(String principalName,
                          Object parsedFileContents,
                          String fileUserIdentifer)
Builds the file name using the following construction: All collector files start with gl_collectorflatfile_ append the chartorg from the batch header append the username of the user who is uploading the file then the user supplied indentifier finally the timestamp

Parameters:
user - who uploaded the file
parsedFileContents - represents collector batch object
userIdentifier - user identifier for user who uploaded file
Returns:
String returns file name using the convention mentioned in the description

validate

public boolean validate(Object parsedFileContents)
Description copied from interface: BatchInputFileType
Performs specific validation on the parsed file contents. If errors were found, method will return false and GlobalVariables.errorMap will contain the error message. If no errors were encountered the method will return true.
